<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Default.HideFromAllOutput">
  <body>
    <p>The <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.cloud_agent_short"/> is an important microservice that is required to deploy and manage <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_long"/> (<MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short"/>s). The high-level actions (non-granular calls) that the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.cloud_agent_short"/> makes are limited to the following functions:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Manages the lifecycle and configuration of <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short"/>s in the deployment that includes the creation, deletion, updates, and configuration options on all <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short"/>s in the data center</li>
      <li>Configures Datadog agents. A Datadog agent is part of the deployment that send metrics and monitoring data from an <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short"/> to the central monitoring service. This is required  for an <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short"/>s to be monitored and necessary for <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.cloud_product_short"/> to function. For more information about the central monitoring service and Datadog agents, see <MadCap:xref href="../../../Cloud/Security/security-centralized-monitoring-service.htm"> Centralized Monitoring Service</MadCap:xref>.</li>
      <li>Send system-level diagnostic information of the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short"/>s to the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.home_cloud_long"/> to allow for rapid response to address any issues. Information provided is solely for to help with the recovery of <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short"/>s to save recovery and costs.</li>
      <li>Transfer logs and monitoring traffic to the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.home_cloud_short"/>. No details of the network or personal information is sent.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Depending on deployment configuration, the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.cloud_agent_short"/> typically resides in the same network as where the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short"/>s are deployed. In the following architecture diagram, the red box highlights the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.cloud_agent_short"/>. </p>
    <p>
      <div class="thumbnail-container">
        <img class="solacethumbnail" src="../../Images/Cloud-Security/security_arch_missioncontrolagent.png" alt="Diagram of the Cloud architecture that highlights the Mission Control Agent."/>
      </div>
    </p>
    <p> The <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.cloud_agent_short"/> communication with the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.home_cloud_long"/> is summarized as follows:<br/></p>
    <ul>
      <li>the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.cloud_agent_short"/> always initiates the connection to the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.home_cloud_short"/>. This is a one-way initiation - the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.home_cloud_long"/> never initiates the call.</li>
      <li>the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.cloud_agent_short"/> never transmits any messaging data or personal account information</li>
      <li>the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.cloud_agent_short"/> receives and sends only information related to orchestrating <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short"/>s (includes the creation, deletion, and configuration of <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short"/>s) and monitoring system-level health checks</li>
      <li>the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.cloud_agent_short"/> authenticates with the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.home_cloud_short"/> using an API token, allowing it to connect securely to the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.home_cloud_short"/>'s internal event broker to exchange information; the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.cloud_agent_short"/> does not require a public IP address</li>
    </ul>
    <p> Since the <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.cloud_agent_short"/> is a microservice, it does require a minimal number of permissions to run within the customer's network to manage the lifecycle and configuration of <MadCap:variable name="Product-Names.broker_cloud_short"/>s.</p>
  </body>
</html>
